Reasoning: The paper discusses the development of a visual object recognition system, which involves neural networks and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper focuses on image processing and computer vision, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The use of predictive coding and feature extraction also indicates that the paper could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the discussion of topological structures and connections between different areas of the brain suggests that the paper could also be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
